reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars good size easy setup
reviews.reviewText: larger internal size is very nice. set up was easy even preprogram the start button to desired time for 1 touch start . Really like everything except the display screen is overly bright so no need for a nightlight.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love it…one thing to note….
reviews.reviewText: I love this microwave one because it fits in our built in space. We also ordered the trim kit (not on Amazon as it wasn’t available at the time). I love that it has a 10 second feature in addition to 30 seconds because many times I just need 10, love the modern lighting and seems to have everything I need. 2 cons….1. It’s a little noisy but I’m sure I’m just getting used to a new microwave. 2. It doesn’t fit flush against the trim kit, it sits back (inset a bit like almost an inch. Now maybe the trim kit is off or our space is off or maybe the wrong base was in the trim kit. This is the most annoying thing, but again it could just be our situation. However despite these small minor issues, it’s a win! It’s almost impossible to find one that fits our built in space as the dimensions and design of microwaves has changed. We have modified our space once to accommodate this, but happily we do not have to modify a second time due to this microwave fitting. I should also mention it just really looks modern and seems very high quality. So far heating seems to be good and it’s easy to use. If you are having trouble fitting your built in space, give this one a try. There were only a couple we could even choose from and so happy we chose this.

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Picture is not accurate!
reviews.reviewText: I gave it a 3, but the microwave came damaged (fed ex delivered) so I really don't know how it works. What I do know is that the microwave doesn't have any stainless except for a narrow strip on the bottom. The picture shows stainless along the top and the bottom. It is actually a separate trim kit which is sold separately and expensive. Didn't reorder since it was sold out.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not bad just not impressed
reviews.reviewText: Installation was straightforward. I replaced broken Frigidaire microwave that was broken - same type just much earlier model. I really don’t use it to do much more than popcorn and reheating. Popcorn has 3 different presets for the popular different size bags. I buy the larger bags. However if I use that preset it burns the popcorn. So I started using the preset for the next size down bag. It STILL burns the popcorn! I could have saved myself a LOT of money and purchased a less expensive microwave that would have popped popcorn correctly!
